      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your desire for autonomy, but self-adjusting medication without a clear medical directive can be dangerous. Blood work is one thing, but your body's response to warfarin is complex and can change. A lower dose might seem safer, but it could also lead to under-anticoagulation and increased risk of clotting. Stick to the prescribed regimen and consult your doctor for any changes. Your health is paramount.",
